n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00F8|[[\u00f8]]|248}}\n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00F9|[[\u00f9]]|249}}\n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00FA|[[\u00fa]]|250}}\n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00FB|[[\u00fb]]|251}}\n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00FC|[[\u00fc]]|252}}\n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00FD|[[\u00fd]]|253}}\n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00FE|[[Thorn (letter)|\u00fe]]|254}}\n|{{chset-color-alpha}}|{{chset-cell3|00FF|[[\u00ff]]|255}}\n|}\n{{chset-legend|graybox=Differences from [[ISO-8859-1]]}}\n\n<!-- See {{chset-tableformat}} -->\nAccording to the information on Microsoft's and the Unicode Consortium's websites, positions 81, 8D, 8F, 90, and 9D are unused; however, the Windows API <code>[https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/dd319072%28v=vs.85%29.aspx MultiByteToWideChar]</code> maps these to the corresponding [[C0 and C1 control codes|C1 control code]]s. The \"best fit\" mapping documents this behavior, too.<ref name=bestfit/>\n\n===History===\n* The first version of the codepage 1252 used in Microsoft Windows 1.0 did not have positions D7 and F7 defined. All the characters in the ranges 80\u20139F were undefined too.\n* The second version, used in Microsoft Windows 2.0, positions D7, F7, 91, and 92 had been defined.\n* The third version, used since Microsoft Windows 3.1, had all the present-day positions defined, except [[Euro sign]] and [[\u017d|Z with caron]] character pair.\n* The final version listed above debuted in Microsoft Windows 98 and was ported to older versions of Windows with the Euro symbol update.\n\n==={{anchor|CP1004}}OS/2 extensions===\nThe [[OS/2]] operating system supports an encoding by the name of '''Code page 1004''' or \"Windows Extended\". This mostly matches code page 1252, with the exception of certain [[C0 control characters]] being replaced by [[diacritic]] characters.\n\n{| {{chset-tableformat}}\n{{chset-table-header|Code page 1004 (differing rows only)<ref name=\"ibm1004\">{{cite web |title=Code Page 01004 |publisher=[[IBM]] |url=http://www-03.ibm.com/systems/resources/systems_i_software_globalization_pdf_cp01004z.pdf |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150708030511/http://www-03.ibm.com/systems/resources/systems_i_software_globalization_pdf_cp01004z.pdf |archive-date=2015-07-08}} (version based on Windows 3.1 version of Windows-1252)</ref><ref name=\"borgendale1004\">{{cite web |title=Codepage 1004 - Windows Extended |first=Ken |last=Borgendale |work=OS/2 codepages by number |date=2001 |url=http://www.borgendale.com/codepage/cp1004.gif |access-date=2018-05-13 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180513184106/http://www.borgendale.com/codepage/cp1004.gif |archive-date=2018-05-13}} (version based on current version of Windows-1252)</ref>}}\n|-\n!{{chset-left2|0_<br/>0}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|0000|[[Null character|NUL]]|0}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|0001|[[Start of heading|SOH]]|1}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|0002|[[Start of text|STX]]|2}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|0003|[[End of text|ETX]]|3}}\n|{{chset-color-letter-box|green}}|{{chset-ctrl|02C9||4}}\n|{{chset-color-graph-box|green}}|{{chset-ctrl|02D8||5}}\n|{{chset-color-graph-box|green}}|{{chset-ctrl|02D9||6}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|0007|[[Bell character|BEL]]|7}}\n|{{chset-color-graph-box|green}}|{{chset-ctrl|02DA||8}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|0009|[[Tab character|HT]]|9}}\n|{{chset-color-graph-box|green}}|{{chset-ctrl|02DD||10}}\n|{{chset-color-graph-box|green}}|{{chset-ctrl|02DB||11}}\n|{{chset-color-letter-box|green}}|{{chset-ctrl|02C7||12}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|000D|[[Carriage return|CR]]|13}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|000E|[[Shift out|SO]]|14}}\n|{{chset-color-ctrl}}|{{chset-ctrl|000F|[[Shift in|SI]]|15}}\n|}\n{{Legend-inline|Transparent|border=medium solid green|Differences from Windows-1252}}\n\n==={{anchor|GrCP1252}}MSDOS extensions [rare]===\nThere is a rarely used, but useful, graphics extended code page 1252 where codes 0x00 to 0x1f allow for box drawing as used in applications such as MSDOS Edit and Codeview. One of the applications to use this code page was an Intel Corporation Install/Recovery disk image utility from mid/late 1995. These programs were written for its P6 User Test Program machines (US example<ref name=\"P6 UTP\">{{cite web|url=https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/88a2/d8b2ae94d7e2581fb3e94e2cd71635a8d655.pdf|title=Performance of NASA Equation Solvers on Computational Mechanics Applications|publisher=NASA}}</ref>). It was used exclusively in its then EMEA region (Europe, Middle East & Africa). In time the programs were changed to use code page 850.\n\n{| {{chset-tableformat}}\n{{chset-table-header|Graphics Extended Code Page 1252{{cn|date=October 2019}}}}\n|-\n!{{chset-left2|0_<br/>0}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|25CB}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|25A0}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2191}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2193}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2192}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2190}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2551}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2550}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2554}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2557}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|255A}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|255D}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2591}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2592}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|25BA}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|25C4}}\n|-\n!{{chset-left2|1_<br/>16}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2502}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2500}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|250C}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2510}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2514}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2518}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|251C}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2524}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2534}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|252C}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2666}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|253C}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2588}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2584}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|2580}}\n|{{chset-color-graph}}|{{chset-cell|25AC}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Western Latin character sets (computing)]]\n* [[Windows-1250]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150708030511/http://www-03.ibm.com/systems/resources/systems_i_software_globalization_pdf_cp01252z.pdf IBM's] and [https://web.archive.org/web/20151027124421/https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc195054.aspx Microsoft's] code charts for Windows-1252 (\"Code Page 1252 Windows Latin 1 (ANSI)\")\n* [[International Components for Unicode|ICU]] mapping charts [https://ssl.icu-project.org/icu-bin/convexp?conv=ibm-1252_P100-2000 for the Windows 3.1 version (CCSID 1252)] and the [https://ssl.icu-project.org/icu-bin/convexp?conv=windows-1252 Windows 98 version (CCSID 5348)]\n* [https://www.iana.org/assignments/charset-reg/windows-1252 IANA Charset Name Registration]\n* [https://www.unicode.org/Public/MAPPINGS/VENDORS/MICSFT/WINDOWS/CP1252.TXT Unicode mapping table] and [https://www.unicode.org/Public/MAPPINGS/VENDORS/MICSFT/WindowsBestFit/bestfit1252.txt code page definition with best fit mappings] for Windows-1252\n\n{{Character encoding}}\n\n[[Category:Windows code pages]]\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 1985]]\n", "name_user": "Comp.arch", "label": "safe", "comment": "Stats.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows-1252"}
